00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:50.200
Malaga's history spans about 2800

00:00:50.200 --> 00:00:52.440
years, making it one of the oldest cities

00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:53.880
in Europe and one of the oldest

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:55.760
continuously inhabited cities in the

00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:58.320
world. According to most scholars, it was

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:01.200
founded about 770 BC by the Phoenicians.

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:03.960
From the 6th century BC, the city was

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:05.880
under the Hegemony of ancient Carthage.

00:01:06.190 --> 00:01:08.910
And from 2:18 BC it was ruled by the

00:01:08.910 --> 00:01:11.110
Roman Republic. After the fall of the

00:01:11.110 --> 00:01:13.670
Empire and the end of Visigothic rule, it

00:01:13.670 --> 00:01:16.590
was under Islamic rule for 800 years. But

00:01:16.590 --> 00:01:19.470
in 1487 the crown of Castile gained

00:01:19.470 --> 00:01:21.550
control in the midst of the Granada War.

00:01:21.870 --> 00:01:24.030
The archaeological remains and monuments

00:01:24.030 --> 00:01:26.390
from the Phoenician, Roman, Arabic and

00:01:26.390 --> 00:01:28.390
Christian eras make the historic center

00:01:28.390 --> 00:01:30.670
of the city an open museum displaying its

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:32.630
history of nearly 3000 years.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:36.960
Malaga is an important tourist

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:39.470
destination. Known as the capital of the

00:01:39.470 --> 00:01:42.470
Costa del Sol, an estimated 6,000,000

00:01:42.470 --> 00:01:44.590
tourists visit the city each year.

00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:47.070
Tourists usually visit the Old Town or

00:01:47.070 --> 00:01:49.710
the beaches. The Malaga Harbor is also the

00:01:49.710 --> 00:01:51.990
2nd busiest cruise port of the Iberian

00:01:51.990 --> 00:01:54.950
Peninsula. Beyond its 16 sunny beaches,

